MÉXICO 🇲🇽 Eat the World NYC review: Chasing some ghosts from Michoacán, a couple recent visits instead turned up some really talented chefs and and an interesting 9 year history of this South Sunset Park Mexican restaurant. Originally opening as a fine dining establishment, the city's non-Mexican food media was determined to put these Mexican chefs in their place and called their prices "astronomical" from the beginning. Apparently only white chefs can charge a lot for Mexican food if the Village Voice et al had their way. Well after some years, the menu reads closer to your typical Sunset Park varieties, but there are still some gems and the quality levels are definitely higher than your standard platos fuertes.
